<NOTE>Eds: Members who used BC-JFK-TV Remembers, with a New York
dateline, sent Nov. 1 as b0538 for use beginning Nov. 2, are asked
to use the following:</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported incorrectly on Nov.
2 that the family of John F. Kennedy had cooperated in creation of a
series called ``John Fitzgerald Kennedy: A Celebration of His Life
and Times,'' being broadcast on the Disney Channel this month.
   The Disney Channel acknowledged Thursday that the material used
in the series came from the John F. Kennedy Library and Museum in
Boston, rather than directly from the family of the late president
as it reported in an earlier news release.
