<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--CommunistPresident     11-04 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Communist President,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>UMass Student Senate Bars Avowed Communist From President's Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMHERST, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The University of Massachusetts Student
Senate has barred an avowed communist and his cohort from the
Student Government Association offices they were elected to head.
   Jason Rabinowitz and Shari Silkoff were elected co-presidents of
the student body last March, but the 47-44 vote by the Student
Senate on Wednesday prohibits them from using the title of
co-president.
   Conservatives on the Student Senate contend that two people
cannot not hold one office under the campus constitution.
   ``I think the Student Senate sent a clear message to them that
they aren't co-presidents,'' said Brian Darling, one of the sponsors
of motions to oust Rabinowitz, a member of the Young Communist
League, and Silkoff from office.
   A motion on a new election will be taken up at a Student Senate
meeting Wednesday.
   Silkoff, a self-proclaimed progressive, said after the vote:
``Most of them are new senators and for them to comprehend
everything that has gone on is impossible.''
</TEXT>
