<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Vanna,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Vanna White Sues Electronics Company for Unauthorized Advertisement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vanna White, the letter-turning beauty of
``Wheel of Fortune,'' has filed a $1 million lawsuit against an
electronics company and its advertising agency claiming they are
using her likeness without permission.
   The advertisements selling televisions and stereos for Samsung
Electronics show a likeness of Miss White standing on a copy of the
television game-show set, Miss White's personal manager, Ray
Manzella, said Thursday.
   ``What Samsung has done is unauthorized and they will have to
answer for it,'' he said.
   The suit targets Samsung, of New York, and its advertising
agency, David Deutsch Associates, Inc., also of New York.
   It seeks $1 million in damage and unspecified punitive damages.
   Telephone calls to Samsung were unanswered Thursday evening.
Calls to David Deutsch Associates were referred to company President
Jim Aucone, who was unavailable.
</TEXT>
