<HEAD>Text Of Proposed Palestinian Declaration of Independence</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Israel-Palestinians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is the text of a proposed
Palestinian declaration of independence published today by the
Arabic-language daily Al Fajr newspaper. The text was translated by
The Associted Press.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>Declaration of Independence</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   1. We the Palestinian people represented by the PNC (Palestine
National Council) announce the declaration of the Palestinian State
on the soil of Palestine and with Jerusalem as its capital, all
according to the inherent rights of Palestinians to live in their
homeland in accordance with United Nations Security Council
Resolution 181, published in 1947.
   2. The Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) is the sole
representative for the Palestinian people in accordance with the
decisions of all Arab and Islamic summits, especially the Fez summit.
   3. The PLO calls on Arab and European heads of state, first among
them the two superpowers, to work hard toward implementing all U.N.
resolutions connected to the Palestinian problem and also the Geneva
agreement (on human rights).
   4. The PNC, in announcing the declaration of the independence of
the Palestinian state, insists the only path to solve the problem is
the one of implementing all international resolutions through an
active international conference with the participation of the PLO.
</TEXT>
