<HEAD>Park Intruder Eaten By Lions</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who sneaked into a wild animal park
to steal meat was caught and devoured by lions, a Zimbabwe newspaper
reported today.
   The unidentified intruder's remains were found last week by a
warden at the Lion and Cheetah Park near Harare, The Herald
newspaper said.
   ``He got into a cage with four very bad lions,'' Vivian Bristow,
owner of the park, was quoted as saying. She told the newspaper the
man was believed to have entered the cage to steal meat left for the
animals. There are 32 lions at the park.
   All that remained of the man were bones, an identity card and a
driving license.
