<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--Mayor'sLincoln     11-04 0123</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Mayor's Lincoln,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mayor's Car Stolen, Thief Hangs Up on His Honor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELLFLOWER, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When Mayor Ken Cleveland discovered his
Lincoln Continental had been stolen, he knew exactly how to contact
the thieves.
   He dialed his car phone.
   ``I called it and they answered it. They're so dumb,'' he said.
``It was a guy who answered. He said, `Hello,' and I said, `How you
doing?'
   ``Then he said, `OK,' and hung up.''
   The mayor's TV set, a camera, boxes of fireworks and cases of
beer and wine were also stolen, taken by intruders who entered while
he, his wife and their guests slept, Cleveland said. He discovered
the theft Thursday morning.
   ``I'm just glad no one got hurt,'' he said.
</TEXT>
