<1ST_LINE>r w PM-DollRecall     11-04 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Doll Recall,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tonka Recalls Dolls</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   '
   WASHINGTON (AP) _ ``Love Me Tender'' dolls are being recalled
because the plastic eyes could come off and pose a threat of choking
children, according to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
   Tonka Products launched the recall after receiving 76 reports
from consumers about cases in which the eyes had come off the dolls.
No injuries were reported in any of the cases, the company said.
   More than 100,000 dolls, model numbers 8900 and 8901, have been
sold nationwide since July 1987. They cost between $18 and $30.
   Parents were urged to take the dolls away from young children and
return them to the place of purchase or to Tonka for a refund. The
address to mail back the dolls is Tonka Products, Attention
Department K, 2950 Robertson Ave., Cincinnati, Ohio, 45209.
   Those needing more information can contact the company at
1-800-548-7262 or the safety commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
