<HEAD>Couple Says Objects Fly Around Their Home</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout to UPDATE with police closing investigation.</NOTE>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto PAR1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTPELLIER, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An elderly couple claims objects flew
mysteriously around their home at night and asked police to
investigate.
   The French news agency Agence France-Presse quoted police sources
as saying a doctor examined the woman and determined she was
mentally disturbed. The sources, who were not identified, said they
had no plans to pursue the case.
   ``We've lived here for 50 years and nothing like this ever
happened before,'' 76-year-old Raoul Fournier told reporters
Thursday.
   Fournier said dishes, jars of jelly and other items flew around a
room on the ground floor of the house from 11 p.m. Tuesday until 4
a.m. Wednesday.
   ``It's unimaginable what happened,'' he said. ``Trinkets, dishes
and even our holy candle brought back from Lourdes flew around at
high speed and crashed against the walls.''
   He said his wife Angele, 73, was still shocked by the experience
and did not want to talk about the events. ``Someone cast a spell on
my wife,'' he said. ``But we don't have any enemies.''
   AFP quoted the police sources as saying the man did not see the
events themselves but was old about them by his wife.
</TEXT>
