<HEAD>Cops Say Man Shot Two Daughters And Self</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man accused of raping his 12-year-old
stepdaughter took the girl and her sister hostage in an attic,
shooting to death the stepdaughter and wounding himself and the
other child, police said.
   The shootings occurred Thursday when officers attempted to arrest
Emanuel Shoulders for the alleged rape, said police Sgt. Chip Pippen.
   Shoulders had apparently learned of the arrest warrant sworn out
by his wife and picked up the girls at school, taking them to a
brother-in-law's home, Pippen said.
   Pippen said about a half-hour after police knocked on the door,
they heard gunshots.
   Shoulders was in critical condition at Hinds General Hospital
with a head wound, said hospital spokeswoman Donna Ritchey.
   Six-year-old Latasha Shoulders was in intensive care after
surgery today at the University of Mississippi Medical Center. Dawn
Shoulders died at the hospital.
