<2ND_LINE>AM-Dukakis-Excerpts,340</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Political Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are excerpts from the remarks of
Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis, the Democratic presidential
nominee, at a rally Friday in the Forest Hills section of New York
City:
   ``I like your spirit and I think we're going to win on the 8th of
November, don't you. ... Look at the diversity around us. ... Only
in the Democratic Party could this happen, a son of immigrants the
nominee of his party.
   ... I know the Republicans were celebrating a little prematurely
a couple of weeks ago, popping those champagne corks in their
penthouses. ... We're the ones who are going to be celebrating.
   ... I think Mr. Bush is coasting, we're fighting back all across
the country. He's slipping; we're surging.
   He thinks you can inherit the White House, I think you've got to
earn the right to be president of the United States.
   ... (Republicans) want the American people to forget that they
stole from our children in piling up the biggest debt in history.
... They stole from our future by trashing our environment.
   ... Yesterday, if you can believe this, Mr. Bush took a furlough
from the truth by saying that he was on the side of working American
families, can you believe that. Four days before the election, after
all the symbols and slogans, four days before the election he tells
you he's on your side. Who's he kidding.
   ... 28 years ago, another son of Massaschusetts challenged us to
win the race to the moon and we did. As president, I want to
challenge the people of American to one fundamental goal: drug free
schools in the 1990s.
   ... I'll be damned if I'm going to let them send that stuff into
our country and poison our kids and destroy our neighborhoods.
   ... This election is about the future. It's about our children
and our grandchildren. It's about our neighborhoods and communities.
... and yes, it's about the Supreme Court and who the next
president's going to appoint.
   ... We have four days to go and much to go and remember, the best
American is not behind us, the best America is yet to come.
