<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--MilitaryMoves     11-04 0113</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Military Moves,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Nominates Two Rear Admirals for Promotions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has nominated two rear
admirals to receive their third stars and new assignments, the
Pentagon said Friday.
   Assuming Senate confirmation, Rear Adm. Paul D. Butcher will
become a vice admiral and new chief of the Military Sealift Command,
and Rear Adm. Raymond P. Ilg will become vice admiral and deputy
commander of U.S. Naval Forces, Europe.
   Butcher, 58, is a native of Lundale, W.Va. He is deputy commander
and chief of staff for the U.S. Atlantic Fleet.
   Ilg, 50, is a native of Lowell, Mass. He is the deputy assistant
chief of naval operations for air warfare.
</TEXT>
