<HEAD>Dukakis Widens Lead in Rhode Island poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democrat Michael Dukakis is pulling
slightly ahead of Republican George Bush in Rhode Island, but his
lead is not yet statistically significant, a new poll of
presidential candidates preferred by likely voters indicates.
   The latest poll, released Friday by WPRI-TV, showed Dukakis
leading 48 percent to Bush's 42 percent, statistically too close to
call with a five percentage point margin of error.
   The Massachusetts governor, who had maintained a steady lead in
neighboring Rhode Island in late summer, first fell back late last
month when two successive polls by WPRI showed Dukakis and Bush
nearly even.
   The latest poll was conducted Wednesday and Thursday by Joseph T.
Fleming & Associates and involved a telephone survey of 411 likely
voters.
