<TEXT>
   Sen. Quentin Burdick expected to lead a
Democratic sweep of key statewide offices Tuesday, even though
Republicans counted on keeping the state's three presidential
electoral votes in the GOP column for George Bush.
   In addition to the Senate seat, Democrats were favorites
according to public opinion polls to hold on to the state's lone
U.S. House seat and the governor's office.
