<TEXT>
   The following figures, provided by the
Welsh Office, show the rise in Wales' gross domestic product, the
sum of all is goods and services, over a 15-year period. (Dollar
figures are at the current exchange rate.)
   1986 _ 13.5 billion pounds ($23.9 billion)
   1985 _ 12.68 billion pounds ($22.4 billion)
   1984 _ 11.01 billion bounds ($19.5 billion)
   1983 _ 10.64 billion pounds ($18.8 billion)
   1982 _ 9.67 billion pounds ($17.1 billion)
   1981 _ 8.73 billion pounds ($15.5 billion)
   1976 _ 4.91 billion pounds ($8.7 billion)
   1971 _ 2.15 billion pounds ($3.8 billion)
