<HEAD>London Shares Off 3.3 Points</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: Updates throughout with close, no pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices finished lower on London's Stock
Exchange Friday, as the release of stronger-than-expected U.S.
unemployment figures curbed the market's earlier gains.
   The London market followed Wall Street downward after the release
of the report. It also followed Wall Street back up, when New York
staged a partial recovery.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed down
3.3 points, or 0.2 percent, at 1,834.3. Volume was 566.7 million
shares, up from 507.5 million shares a day earlier.
   Several traders said they were cautiously optimistic during the
morning session, but the release of the unemployment data knocked
the market lower in the afternoon. The news that the U.S. jobless
rate fell to 5.3 percent in October from 5.4 percent in the previous
month rekindled fears that the U.S. economy might be overheating.
</TEXT>
